org.gradoop.flink.model.impl.operators.layouting

Class FusingFRLayouter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gradoop.flink.model.impl.operators.layouting.FRLayouter
      • org.gradoop.flink.model.impl.operators.layouting.FusingFRLayouter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Operator, UnaryBaseGraphToBaseGraphOperator<LogicalGraph>, UnaryBaseGraphToValueOperator<LogicalGraph,LogicalGraph>, UnaryGraphToGraphOperator, LayoutingAlgorithm

    public class FusingFRLayouter
extends FRLayouter
    A special variant of the FRLayouter that combines similar vertices during the layouting, creating a simplified version of the graph.

      • FusingFRLayouter

        public FusingFRLayouter(int iterations,
                        int vertexCount,
                        double threshold,
                        FusingFRLayouter.OutputFormat outputFormat)
        Create new FusingFRLayouter
        Parameters:
        iterations - Number of iterations to perform
        vertexCount - Number of vertices in the input-graph (used to compute default-values)
        threshold - Only vertices with a similarity of at least threshold are combined. Lower values will lead to a more simplified output-graph. Valid values are >= 0 and <= 1 .
        outputFormat - Chosen OutputFormat. See FusingFRLayouter.OutputFormat

      • applyForces

        protected org.apache.flink.api.java.DataSet<LVertex> applyForces(org.apache.flink.api.java.DataSet<LVertex> vertices,

                                                                 int iterations)
        Description copied from class: FRLayouter
        Applies the given forces to the given vertices.
        Overrides:
        applyForces in class FRLayouter
        Parameters:
        vertices - Vertices to move
        forces - Forces to apply. At most one per vertex. The id indicates which vertex the force should be applied to
        iterations - Number of iterations that will be performed (NOT the number of the current iteration). It is used to compute the simulated annealing shedule.
        Returns:
        The input vertices with x and y coordinated changed according to the given force and current iteration number.
